'''The Malaria Policy Advisory Committee''' is an international organization that works to prevent [[malaria]].
The [[World Health Organization]] presently works with international MPAC members, led by Doctor Salim Abdulla, for initiatives such as the fight against [[malaria]]. Members are from countries which include; [[Tanzania]], [[Spain]], [[Ghana]], [[Australia]], [[England]], [[Cameroon]], [[Sudan]], [[Kenya]], [[Sri Lanka]], The [[Philippines]], [[Switzerland]], [[India]], and [[Thailand]].<ref>http://www.who.int/malaria/mpac/mpacmembers/en/index.html</ref>
